with a first-order fresnel lens.

09:15.622 --> 09:18.290
- No, no.
The fresnel lens is incredible.

09:18.292 --> 09:20.292
Fresnel was
this french physicist

09:20.294 --> 09:22.193
Who had the idea
to take a glass lens

09:22.195 --> 09:24.162
And cut grooves in it
in concentric circles.

09:24.164 --> 09:25.897
And each groove
acts like a prism

09:25.899 --> 09:27.165
That refracts the source light

09:27.167 --> 09:28.900
And concentrates it into a beam

09:28.902 --> 09:30.101
That can be seen
much further away

09:30.103 --> 09:32.170
Using a much thinner piece
of glass.

09:32.172 --> 09:34.806
And the first-order lens,
which is what this is,

09:34.808 --> 09:38.043
Is the biggest one 'cause it's
got a prismatic dome on top.

09:38.045 --> 09:41.846
You can see it from, like,
30 miles.

09:41.848 --> 09:45.317
I'm sorry.
