47:47.098 --> 47:50.099
- Two years ago.

47:50.101 --> 47:53.903
- [sighs]

47:53.905 --> 47:56.973
How old was he?

47:56.975 --> 48:00.042
- Four.

48:00.044 --> 48:02.245
He'd be six now.

48:02.247 --> 48:05.314
He'd be learning to read.

48:07.351 --> 48:09.518
- What was his name?

48:12.956 --> 48:14.891
- Gabriel.

48:22.332 --> 48:24.500
- What was he like?

48:30.040 --> 48:31.307
- He...

48:31.309 --> 48:34.443
He was perfect.

48:34.445 --> 48:36.512
God, he had these...

48:36.514 --> 48:40.616
He had these wide,
green eyes...

48:40.618 --> 48:43.152
And he thought
everything was funny.

48:43.154 --> 48:44.654
[laughs]

48:44.656 --> 48:48.024
He never wanted to be
left out of a joke.

48:50.994 --> 48:54.196
When I wake up,

48:54.198 --> 48:57.266
Before I open my eyes, I...

48:57.268 --> 49:00.002
I listen for his laugh...

49:00.004 --> 49:03.139
Because I'd gotten
so used to hearing it, you know?

49:03.141 --> 49:05.408
That's how every morning started
for so long.

49:05.410 --> 49:07.410
I'd wake up,

49:07.412 --> 49:10.413
And he'd be standing there
at the bed,

49:10.415 --> 49:13.516
Looking at me and laughing.

49:13.518 --> 49:17.687
He thought it was so funny
that grown-ups sleep too.

49:22.426 --> 49:24.327
Now when I open my eyes,

49:24.329 --> 49:28.164
My house is so quiet.

49:28.166 --> 49:32.568
Cole has this tattoo on his back
of the angel gabriel.

49:32.570 --> 49:35.104
It's the first thing I see
every fucking morning,

49:35.106 --> 49:38.641
And it all comes rushing back,
and I want to die.

49:46.350 --> 49:49.218
- I'm so sorry.

49:51.321 --> 49:54.056
- So now you know.

49:54.058 --> 49:59.128
I cut myself once in a while
because it makes me feel better.

50:05.602 --> 50:08.771
I'll understand
if I never see you again.

50:22.619 --> 50:25.021
- I'll take you home.

50:30.560 --> 50:33.662
[engine turning over]

50:41.204 --> 50:42.772
Where is cole?

50:42.774 --> 50:46.042
- He went to syracuse
to pick up a new horse.

50:46.044 --> 50:49.111
He won't be back
till tomorrow night.

51:01.324 --> 51:03.426
Uh, I need my bike.
[chuckles]

51:03.428 --> 51:04.727
- Right.

51:04.729 --> 51:06.729
Idiot.

51:25.415 --> 51:27.516
Right here?

51:27.518 --> 51:29.685
- Thanks.

51:40.764 --> 51:43.599
Noah...

51:43.601 --> 51:45.501
Thank you...

51:45.503 --> 51:48.537
For today.

51:48.539 --> 51:50.239
I'm--I'm sorry if I--

51:50.241 --> 51:52.308
- No, no, no.

51:52.310 --> 51:54.343
Don't apologize.

51:59.616 --> 52:02.418
- Can I ask you something?

52:02.420 --> 52:05.321
- Anything.

52:05.323 --> 52:07.356
- What do you see now...

52:07.358 --> 52:10.192
When you look at me?

52:14.731 --> 52:17.266
- What do you think I see?

52:21.304 --> 52:23.305
- Death.

52:26.610 --> 52:29.812
- No.

52:31.214 --> 52:33.349
- What do you see, then?

52:51.368 --> 52:55.437
You don't want this.

52:55.439 --> 52:59.308
- Alison, I'm a grown man.
I know what I want.

53:30.807 --> 53:34.210
[both breathing heavily]

53:50.327 --> 53:52.561
Look at me.

53:52.563 --> 53:56.765
Look at me.

53:56.767 --> 53:58.934
Look at me.

54:39.776 --> 54:42.945
[both moaning]
